description: {"blocks":[{"key":"56fqd","text":"In order to carry out the research project of genetic adaptation to high-altitude hypoxia in Sherpa highlanders, we recruited Sherpa highlanders in Namche Bazaar village at a high altitude of 3,440 meters (m) above sea level and non-Sherpa lowlanders in Kathmandu city at 1,300 m in Nepal. Venous blood was sampled to obtain plasma and extract DNA in each subject. The concentrations of factors in plasma were measured.  The single-nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) in the hypoxia-associated genes were genotyped.  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6rhef","text":"Recruiting Sherpa highlanders in Namche Bazaar village (3,440 m) in the Solu-Khumbu region in Nepal.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2djpf","text":"The Sherpas in Namche Bazaar village voluntarily participated in this investigation.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4jlaq","text":"The Sherpa clan was identified with the Sherpa surname and confirmed by a senior native Sherpa.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"fdvb9","text":"All Sherpas were born and permanently resided in Namche Bazaar.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8cloh","text":"They were unrelated to each other in the first and second degree and had no history of intermarriage with other ethnic groups.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b4rv4","text":"They did not leave their residences within three months of the sample collections.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4nvas","text":"Information regarding demographics, health status, altitude of residence, occupation, and mountaineering history was obtained during an interview.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ke9e","text":"Symptoms of chronic mountain sickness (CMS), such as headache, dizziness, dyspnea, sleep disturbances, physical and mental fatigue, and cyanosis were specifically evaluated during the interviews.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"b8gjl","text":"A percutaneous arterial oxygen saturation (SpO2) and pulse rate were measured using a pulse oximeter (Pulsox-3, Minolta, Osaka, Japan) with a probe connecting to a finger.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cct9u","text":"Venous blood samples were taken and placed in tubes containing ethylenediaminetetraacetic acid (EDTA) anticoagulant for plasma sampling and DNA extraction.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"v5g","text":"The plasma was separated from the whole blood by centrifuging for 10 minutes at 3,000 rpm using a portable centrifuge at the site. The pelleted leukocytes were used for DNA extraction.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fmd9u","text":"The plasma samples and the precipitation were stored in a freezer at \u003c −20 °C until measurements of factors in plasma and DNA extraction.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"bc0bc","text":"Recruiting Non-Sherpa lowlanders in Kathmandu (1,300 m) in Nepal.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ar7s","text":"The non-Sherpa Nepalese were identified by their languages and social status (caste groups) with the help of native Nepalese.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6gg3b","text":"They did not travel to high altitudes within three months of the sample collections.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"5sorv","text":"The protocol of recruitments and sample collections for the non-Sherpa lowlanders was followed as that for the Sherpa highlanders in Namche Bazaar.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"8h4r6","text":"All the samples were transported in frozen status from Namche Bazaar to Kathmandu by porters, and then to Japan by air cargo.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"rp48","text":"The experiments were undertaken in our laboratory at Shinshu University, Matsumoto (600 m), Japan.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1mr7k","text":"The concentrations of factors in plasma were measured using the quantitative sandwich ELISA kit following the manufacturer’s instructions.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"aipvg","text":"The genomic DNA was extracted from venous blood leukocytes by phenol extraction of sodium dodecyl sulfate-lysed and proteinase K-treated cells.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cn9vd","text":"Allele discrimination was performed using the TaqMan® SNP Genotyping Assay with the Applied Biosystems 7500 Fast Real-time PCR System (Applied Biosystems Inc. Foster City, CA, USA) following the manufacturer’s instructions.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"1v63f","text":"After thermal cycling, genotype data were automatically acquired and analyzed using sequence detection software (SDS v1.3.1; Applied Biosystems, Inc.).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
